vaoptions_basemap_help: A basemap from arcgis.com. Ignored if portalItemId is set.
vaoptions_visualizationType_help: The kind of the SAS-generated layer to be added to the map.  Optional.
vaoptions_use3D_help: Display the map in a 3D scene view.
vaoptions_title_help: The title of the layer that includes report data. Optional. Defaults to the Geo ID column name, if available, or to "SAS VA Layer", if not.
vaoptions_zIndex_help: The index of the layer that includes report data. Optional. Use 0 to insert the layer below all others. Defaults to the top-most level.
vaoptions_x_help: The label of the column containing longitude expressed in the same terms as the base map. Defaults to "Longitude". Required for coordinates and bubbles visualizations.
vaoptions_y_help: The label of the column containing latitude expressed in the same terms as the base map. Defaults to "Latitude". Required for coordinates and bubbles visualizations.
vaoptions_size_help: The label of the column containing the size measurement. Required for bubble visualizations.
vaoptions_color_help: The label of the column containing the color measurement. Optional for bubble and choropleth visualizations.
vaoptions_animation_help: The label of the column containing the date used when animating through the data. Optional. Animations are not currently supported in choropleths or 3D views, and they should be considered experimental.  Acceptable date formats include RFC2822 and ISO.
vaoptions_period_help: Defines the interval used to subdivide the animation date. Valid values are units of time such as "millisecond", "day", "month", and "year". Defaults to "year".
vaoptions_colorMin_help: A hex ("#bfe4e7"), rgba ("rgba(191,228,231,1)"), or named ("LightCyan") color for the minimum value of the range.
vaoptions_colorMax_help: A hex ("#bfe4e7"), rgba ("rgba(191,228,231,1)"), or named ("LightCyan") color for the maximum value of the range.
vaoptions_outline_help: A hex ("#bfe4e7"), rgba ("rgba(191,228,231,1)"), or named ("LightCyan") color for borders of drawn shapes.
vaoptions_geoId_help: The label of the column containing the geographic identifiers for the areas to be drawn. Required for visualization types "Regions" and "Filtered Esri layer".
vaoptions_featureServiceUrl_help: The url to the Esri feature service containing the shapes of the geographies identified by the Geo ID column name.  Required for visualization types "Regions" and "Filtered Esri layer".
vaoptions_featureServiceGeoId_label: Feature service Geo ID column name:
vaoptions_featureServiceGeoId_help: The name of the attribute in the Esri feature service that will match values found in the Geo ID column of the report's data.  Required for visualization types "Regions" and "Filtered Esri layer".
vaoptions_featureServiceWhere_help: A optional where clause to be provided to the Esri feature service that filters results.
vaoptions_featureServiceMaxAllowableOffs: The optional maxAllowableOffset provided to the feature service. Can be used to restrict the amount of detail (and thus transmission size) of the geographic shapes it returns.  Use 0 to return highest detail.  Defaults to level matching initial extent.
vaoptions_portalItemId_help: The optional ID for a web map provided by the Esri portal (arcgis.com, by default).
vaoptions_portalToken_help: The Esri token string that can be presented to the portal for access.
vaoptions_portalUrl_help: The full URL to the Esri portal.  Defaults to "http://www.arcgis.com".
